comments: Butler (WAS) is turning slightly when marginal body contact occurs with Terry's (CHI) side during the drive.
Terry's (CHI) off-arm slightly extends forward prior to marginal contact occurring with Butler's (WAS) right arm/side as Terry changes direction at the end of the drive.
Butler (WAS) jumps from point A to point B and initiates body contact with Terry (CHI) that alters the driving shot attempt.
Baldwin (WAS) raises his hand up toward the ball and marginal contact occurs with Craig's (CHI) right arm as Vukcevic (WAS) cleanly dislodges the ball away from Craig.
Terry (CHI) is established in Avdija's (WAS) path and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs as they come together in the lane.
Carter (CHI) brushes Vukcevic's (WAS) left arm and Vukcevic is able to move through the marginal contact to continue toward the basket after his gather.
Avdija (WAS) initiates contact with Sanogo's (CHI) left wrist during Sanogo's upward shooting motion.
Vukcevic (WAS) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Vukcevic (WAS) jumps forward slightly to contest the dunk attempt and marginal contact occurs with Terry (CHI) as Terry finishes at the rim.
Butler (WAS) moves to slip behind Craig (CHI) and incidental body contact occurs when they come together inside the perimeter.
Davis (WAS) grasps and then quickly releases Drell's (CHI) left arm during the inbound.
Davis (WAS) commits a take foul on Drell (CHI).
Avdija (WAS) commits a take foul on Terry (CHI).
Vukcevic (WAS) commits a take foul on Sanogo (CHI).
Drell (CHI) engages and disengages with Baldwin Jr. (WAS) as Baldwin Jr. moves to set the pick.
Drell (CHI) moves laterally into Avdija's (WAS) path and is not in a legal guarding position when contact occurs with Avdija's front and left side after his gather.
Vukcevic (WAS) commits a take foul on Sanogo (CHI).

Terry (CHI) is moving alongside Kispert's (WAS) path with a forearm placed against his body and after the release of the shot attempt, follows through and slight contact occurs to Kispert's face.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Drell (CHI) brings his left hand up to Vukcevic's (WAS) right shoulder and marginal contact occurs prior to Drell cleanly cleanly deflecting the ball away.
